*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Business is booming! Pollnivneach has never seen this number of visitors.
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' In fact I'm thinking of expanding and trying to break into the camel hire market.
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' If only I could figure out how to get people to return the camels...
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Is there anything else I can help you with?
*** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Tell me about this town.}}
** '''Player:''' Tell me about this town.
** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Well, Pollnivneach is a funny little place. It's a small town and you'd think it'd be nice and quiet.
** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' But those Menaphites and bandits are making the place quite unbearable.
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|In what way?}}
*** '''Player:''' In what way?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Well, one group is as bad as the other! They steal, they fight, they cause trouble with us locals. Just yesterday one of those bandits came looking for protection money!
*** '''Player:''' Why don't the authorities stop this?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' We're a small town. We don't have the resources to keep the gangs off our backs! Menaphos and Al Kharid are no help either.
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' To tell the truth we live in hope that an outsider, someone with no ties to either group, could broker a deal to halt the hostilities between them.
*** '''Player:''' Hmm...
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Is there anything else I can help you with?
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Well the weak will always be trodden on. Why not stand up to them?}}
*** '''Player:''' Well the weak will always be trodden on. Why not stand up to them?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' That's a little unfair, my friend. We can't all be brave adventurers. If we were, where would you purchase quality camels at discounted prices?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' You might think about that. Anyway, isn't it the job of the brave adventurer to protect the weak and innocent from evil and harm?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Is there anything else I can help you with?
*** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|Perhaps I could help.}}
*** '''Player:''' Perhaps I could help.
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Yes, perhaps you could.
*** '''Player:''' You know the politics better than I do. What do you recommend?
*** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Me?! I am but a humble discount camel seller. You're the adventurer, don't you know what to do?
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|Of course I know what to do! I was just testing you!}}
**** '''Player:''' Of course I know what to do! I was just testing you!
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' That is reassuring to hear. Too often one meets brainless adventurers whose solution to every problem is to hack, maim and murder.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' I'm glad to know you're not of that ilk.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Is there anything else I can help you with?
**** {{tact|above}}
*** {{topt|Perhaps I should know, but offered advice should never be shunned.}}
**** '''Player:''' Perhaps I should know, but offered advice should never be shunned.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' The state of adventurers today. They need everything spelled out for them.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' What, you want me to put a little note in your quest journal?
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' But fine, I'll give you a hint. Try and see if you can get the gangs to agree to a truce by offering them each a token gift as an act of reconciliation.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' If that fails to work, you must consider trying to influence the gangs from within.
**** '''Ali the Camel Man:''' Is there anything else I can help you with?
**** {{tact|above}}
