===Talking to a Menaphite Thug===
* '''Player:''' Hello.
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' What do you want?
* '''Player:''' I am trying to figure out the feud that exists between you and the Bandits.
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' Not much to figure out there, the problem is those thieving bandits.
* '''Player:''' In what way?
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' They are always stealing, starting fights and disrupting the lives of the townsfolk.
* '''Player:''' Word has it that the Menaphites are also involved in unsavoury behaviour.
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' Well, we also steal, start fights, and disrupt lives - but we do it with class! And the bandits definitely started it.
* '''Player:''' How did 'they' start it?
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' I can scarcely remember, it's been so long.
* '''Player:''' Go on try.
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' I think our leader once mentioned that they robbed one of our camels. A heinous crime around these parts.
* '''Player:''' So if they offered a camel as a gesture of goodwill would you agree to cease hostilities?
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' Those bandits would never agree to that. They couldn't afford even the mangiest excuse for a camel, never mind the desert traversing, four legged beauty that we would demand.
* '''Player:''' But if they did?
* '''Menaphite Thug:''' Well, I suppose so.
<!--Varbit 315 changed: 1 -> 3-->
<!--Varbit 334 changed: 2 -> 3-->
* '''Player:''' Maybe if I got both gangs a camel, I could use the mutual good will to find out what happened to Ali's nephew.
* {{tact|end}}
<!--Notes: I believe that if you talk to a Menaphite Thug first, it updates Varbit 315 to 2 at the end of the dialogue, and updates to 3 once you speak to a Bandit. Only after you've spoken to both and Varbit 334 has progressed does the player give their "Maybe if I got..." musing.-->
<!--Speaking to either group again repeats the dialogue with the "Maybe if I got..." bit at the end.-->

